<script>
 $(function(){
  $('.cell').click(function(){
    $(this).toggleClass('alive');
  });
 });
</script>

<div class="conways">
  <h1 class="page-title">Conway's Game of Life</h1>
  <p>Rather than running through scenarios on scrap paper, use the board below.</p>

  <p>I also wrote <a href="/post/tips-for-conways-game-of-life" target="_blank">a post</a> with suggested steps for newer devs and their mentors (TL;DR: don't dive straight into TDD).</p>

  <h3>Rules:</h3>
  <p>If a <strong>live</strong> cell has <strong>two or three</strong> neighbours, it lives. Otherwise, it dies.</p>
  <p>If a <strong>dead</strong> cell has <strong>exactly three</strong> neighbours, it comes to life.</p>

  <div class="conways_world">
    <% for y in 0..9 %>
      <% for x in 0..9 %>
        <div class="cell">
          <%= x %>, <%= y %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
      <div style="clear: both;"></div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>


